<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
	<meta http-equiv="content-type" content="text/html;charset=UTF-8" />
	
	<title><%= render :partial => 'shared/title' %></title>
	
	<!--[if IE]>
		<script src="http://html5shiv.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/html5.js"></script>
  <![endif]-->
	
	<%= javascript_include_tag 'application' %>

	<%= yield :head %>
	
	<%= stylesheet_link_tag 'application' %>
	
	<%= csrf_meta_tag %>
	
	<!--[if IE]>
		<link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="stylesheets/ie7.css" />
	<![endif]-->
</head>
<body>
	<%= render :partial => 'shared/top_bar' %>
	
	<div id="page">
		<div id="back_bar"></div>
		
		<%- if css_naked? -%>
			<div>
				<strong>Today is CSS Naked Day!</strong> Which means that all stylesheets have been turned off for the day so that people can 
				admire the HTML goodness that you don't get to see every day.  A well coded site will remain usable, if not attractive, even
				without their styles in place. Enjoy and know that everything will be back to normal tomorrow.
			</div>
		<%- end -%>
		
		<div id="ie_warning">
			<h3>This site doesn't work well in Internet Explorer.</h3>
			<p>
				I have not tested or made any real effect to make this site work correctly in Internet Explorer (IE).
				Unfortunately, IE fails to implement many web standards that have been supported by virtually ALL other 
				browsers for many years. I would recommend that you change to a different browser like 
				<a href="http://www.apple.com/safari/download/">Safari</a>,
				<a href="http://www.google.com/chrome">Chrome</a>,
				<a href="http://www.getfirefox.com">FireFox</a>, 
				or <a href="http://www.opera.com/">Opera</a>.  All are free and very good.
			</p>
		</div>
		
		<div id="header"><%= render :partial => 'shared/header' %></div>
		
		<div id="content">
			<noscript>
				<ul id="javascript_warning">
					<li>
						You must enable javascript for this site to function properly!
					</li>
				</ul>
			</noscript>
			
			<%= render :partial => 'shared/messages' %>

			<%= yield  %>
		</div>
	</div>
	
	<hr/>
	
	<%= render :partial => 'shared/footer' %>
</body>
</html>
